<subSubSection id="10F94DE47FA05F0BEDF58ADF9D2A24DB" pageId="null" pageNumber="568" type="description">
<paragraph id="BD6408C38B8B6F740E087EFD834E7E54" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="555BC5B0666B147113A1DAD7CBE5C101" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="568" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angulosum">
<emphasis id="D7F87859D90CDB90EC47EE1E900F94F9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">A. angulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 11 d) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<normalizedToken id="E0B68DF50C9E35951DDD44F1FB5D9F2E" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
unterseits 
<emphasis id="9FEDC89C0D80E34A021B34B26FACAC72" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">
ohne deutlichen Kiel; 
<normalizedToken id="C4E3E9F9684E1750E171A67B4E55A773" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
das Perigon weit 
<normalizedToken id="24DC0577739146E8C557178166BBC0B7" originalValue="überragend" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">ueberragend</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="2DE4745AEDE32FD8115FCDE1339D3FEE" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F24905015776DEBD185CE9821BF4E29" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="94008B6E433716BA338E37AC13C4A8CE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 24:</emphasis>
Material aus Ungarn (Baksay 1956). 
<emphasis id="AA62F6B3610936A9D0863FC138609554" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">2n = 32:</emphasis>
Material aus Skandinavien (
<normalizedToken id="EFD4CA7847D5B657429A42A311219E1A" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="4C610E642F6423EB02E0F08A398498F6" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1942b), aus der Schweiz und Schweden, Fortpflanzung normal sexuell (
<normalizedToken id="555990D5DF4117EAB1DEEC0B17293838" originalValue="Håkansson" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Hakansson</normalizedToken>
1951), aus Ungarn (Baksay 1956). 
<emphasis id="CD7277D53D1D7196BCC2E1061D2DEF4E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">2n = 48:</emphasis>
Material aus botanischen 
<normalizedToken id="9ADCD7FE2A637305C8B76511B6244440" originalValue="Gärten" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Gaerten</normalizedToken>
(Mensinkai 1940). Apomiktische Sippen (Ved 1965).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A745E7FB6011D94E6CBEC01D3932BFAD" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="F0EBD9731CF169A389F21259882B8D0B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. Trockene, 
<normalizedToken id="0F2DDA9107C3102301322A9315D18548" originalValue="flachgründige" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">flachgruendige</normalizedToken>
, steinige, locker beraste 
<normalizedToken id="903B458A9C0499B29C75C6A71C83CE0D" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Boeden</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="E0DF8DB5D553463FC16CE5A3BF0A7052" originalValue="Felsbänke" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Felsbaenke</normalizedToken>
und Felsspalten. Trockenwiesen, 
<normalizedToken id="E2770C2792AFED24EA1849BDA64348ED" originalValue="Föhrenwälder" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Foehrenwaelder</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE9C67ED5801319EEF7F464A6FD87E59" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="CB0DF84AA9B25185E9B37C48EB5636E3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Verbreitung. Eurasiatische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Nordgrenze durch 
<normalizedToken id="FBDA29923B4A6CBFC7C5362DB438A2E6" originalValue="Süd-" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Sued-</normalizedToken>
und Mittelfrankreich, Rheinland, Norddeutschland, 
<normalizedToken id="F4EB9F938F42C014C961AA0630CD8EDD" originalValue="Südskandinavien" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Suedskandinavien</normalizedToken>
, Zentralpolen, 
<normalizedToken id="E7568A9D739B3265B324872A5F059962" originalValue="Südrußland" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Suedrussland</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="4A2D669BFBE0BF64EDF7DAFE2186D965" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
zwischen 35 und 55° NB bis an die ostasiatischen 
<normalizedToken id="C9A425D53693BF56C0F6868AF0AA393D" originalValue="Küsten" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Kuesten</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="FAC99B3CE148C7797CAC34EAEC280B4B" originalValue="Südgrenze" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Suedgrenze</normalizedToken>
durch Mittelspanien, 
<normalizedToken id="0D2BD269CBD8E31ABDB300D44BA7655D" originalValue="Süditalien" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Sueditalien</normalizedToken>
, Griechenland, 
<normalizedToken id="B721E5B270743170E3FABDBC156EA010" originalValue="nördliche" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">noerdliche</normalizedToken>
Teile der Balkanhalbinsel, Ukraine, Krim (im Kaukasus 
<taxonomicName id="C499CCE5838888C97B47274DD3E9EFCC" authority="Fisch." authorityName="Fisch." class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="568" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albidum">
<emphasis id="039791ABE3B19BA898B0104BBBCE6D22" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">A. albidum</emphasis>
Fisch.
</taxonomicName>
). Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - Im Gebiet zerstreut, nicht 
<normalizedToken id="C4CE50905F3540D12020080F55F90AAF" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">haeufig</normalizedToken>
; aus Vogesen und Schwarzwald nicht angegeben.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA07703539C7EB707C34D423496DE6C8" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="472F822F3A7A14CA91EC89CE52F91F7E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Die in 
<taxonomicName id="8E4353904F395537A1050979D16DCFE3" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
verbreitete Sippe wird heute vom asiatischen 
<taxonomicName id="197FCD2680232E45510D1C428E7A257F" authority="L." authorityName="L." class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="568" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="senescens">
<emphasis id="EA7A65E50297144462627A4195878D6A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">A. senescens</emphasis>
<authorityName id="A01C1407B8E719A859C58E2BFB29D086" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">L.</authorityName>
</taxonomicName>
als so verschieden betrachtet, 
<normalizedToken id="3893DBE250E2BAEE0431E170710496AF" originalValue="daß" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">dass</normalizedToken>
sie als Art, 
<taxonomicName id="2FB8557980BCAE06E010BA02634530FE" authority="Schmidt" authorityName="Schmidt" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="568" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montanum">
<emphasis id="8D82C43B9707445B5013995425FCBB62" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="568">A. montanum</emphasis>
Schmidt
</taxonomicName>
, abgetrennt wird.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
